RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 30. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LYRICAL chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn, gained ground in the lane and dueled to the wire to just hold the win. CELESTIAL ORB trailed the field through the opening quarter of a mile, switched out to the five path to began a bid approaching the quarter pole, lugged in in upper stretch and gained ground to the finish to narrowly miss. MOON ME AGAIN tracked the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend, dueled in the lane, was caught in the final sixteenth of a mile and kept on from there. TAKESTWOTOWIGGLE led the way through the early going, dueled from the two path around the turn, dug in entering the stretch and weakened in the final strides. JLO CAN DANCE raced off the pace up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and showed no kick. BAYOU MELODY stalked the pacesetter on the outside through the opening stages, raced in the four path around the turn and faded in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 30 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered I n Allowances) (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PEARLINTHEROUGH raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the four path, began a bid passing the eighth pole and gained ground late to get up near the wire. HIGH ARABIAN dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path coming around the turn, kicked clear in upper stretch and was caught late. LADYNESS raced off the pace on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the three path and improved position on the rail in the stretch. WIN OR CELLAR pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and kept on to the finish. COUNTLESS DREAMS raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and continued to improve position in the stretch. DELTA RED raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the bend and was outkicked in the lane. NICOLINO dueled between horses up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the turn and tired in the stretch.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Brandywine Farm (Jim & Pam Robinson) & Tiznow Syndicate

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 15350. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 30 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered I n Weight Allowances) (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GARMENTO raced in the three path around the first turn, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far bend, dueled in the stretch and edged clear late. LEOPARDI saved ground early, led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the far bend and in upper stretch and gave way late. TAPINTOYOURBEER bumped with the horse to his outside at the start, recovered to press the pace from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the four path around the far turn and weakened further in the lane. CALZONE bumped with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, raced in the two path around the first bend, tracked the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the three path and was outkicked in the stretch. SHIPWRECK raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn in the four path and faded in the lane. COLORS saved ground around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, dropped back to trail the field from the rail coming around the far bend and continued to tire from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 22500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Two Such Races Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered) (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COPAZO raced in the two path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the four path, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and kicked clear. COCO SHELL led the way from the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the far bend and in upper stretch and chased the winner home late. CESAR saved ground early, tracked the leaders between horses up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the two path and was outkicked in the lane. GODS GLORY raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the second bend and weakened in the stretch. GO GREEN raced in the four path around the first turn, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the far turn and faded in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG BUCKSALOT bumped with the horse to his inside at the start, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn, kicked clear in the stretch and drew off in the final furlong. PRINCE GHOST bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, raced off the pace early, began a bid from the four path coming around the bend and gained ground late. SECOND WAVE led the way through the opening stages, dueled from the three path headed into the turn, was caught in midstretch and kept on from there. NICO'S HAVING FUN chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the turn and kept on in the lane. TIZ A TALE raced off the pace on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued around the bend in the two path and gained ground mildly late. INSTIGATING broke sharply and then quickly dropped back to trail the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and improved position mildly in the lane. TRIPP WILDCAT raced at the back of the pack early, navigated the turn from the three path and passed tiring horses in the lane while never threatening. GRAND SLAM BOY hopped up leaving the gate, settled in the middle of the pack between horses for the run up the backstretch, came around the turn in the three path and was outkicked from there. FAVORITE LIGHT raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening stages, saved ground around the bend and faded in the stretch. GOLD FOR MY LADY was away from the gate slowly, urged up the rail to duel on the inside approaching the turn, raced in the two path from there and tired in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 18500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $25,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $25,000 Or More.). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIRANDA'S ROCKY raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far bend still in the three path, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and held off a closer at the finish while drifting late. MOST DIVINE raced in the two path around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the four path, began a bid entering the stretch and gained ground late. MY JUNE BUG saved ground around the first turn, chased the leaders up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the four path and kept on in the lane. BELLA FACCIA pressed the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn in the two path and weakened late. MOONSHINING raced in the two path early, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, gave way while saving ground around the far bend and continued to fade in the stretch. BRITTY raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, dropped back quickly to trail the field from the rail headed into the far turn and was empty in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Bella Faccia
ENTRY.OWNER: Ciaio Charles A Alexandroff Phyllis and Peterson William P

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $25,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd F or $25,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIR ROBERT HALL veered out at the break, straightened out to chase the leader on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the turn, kicked clear entering the stretch and drew off from there. MOTIVO trailed the field through the early going, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn and gained ground late. SOPHIA'S PRINCE raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and chased on in the stretch. BOLD ADVANCE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, moved up from the two path coming around the turn and was outkicked in the lane. THE GREAT CESAR lugged in a few strides out of the gate, raced off the pace from there, navigated the turn from the three path and never threatened. CITY HUMOR led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the bend and tired in the stretch. VALDOSTA bumped with the horse to his outside at the start, raced in the middle of the pack between horses up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the turn and continued to fade from there. KING SHARK veered in and bumped with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, raced at the back of the pack early, came around the turn in the two path and was empty in the lane.

ENTRY.OWNER: Blazing Meadows Farm LLC and Ella D Racing Stable

ENTRY.NAME: Bold Advance
ENTRY.OWNER: Matalona Thoroughbreds LLC and HMB Racing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at On e Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FEUILLETON saved ground around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, kicked clear while racing on the rail around the far bend and drew off in the lane, in command through the final furlong. FOREVER SAUCY raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far bend and chased the winner home, no match for that rival. KALINBA dueled on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the second turn and weakened in late stretch. MIGHTY FROSTED raced in the four path around the first bend, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the three path and was outkicked in the lane. THE POINT ROAD saved ground at the back of the pack through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn in the three path and passed tiring horses in the lane while never threatening. MY BIG DRAMA raced in the four path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace between horses, saved ground around the second turn and made no bid. RED JET trailed the field from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path and was not a factor. STEEL HAWK saved ground early, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend and was empty in the lane.
